  "market_context": "Uptrend with imperfect structure; price formed a major swing low (origin of BOS), then later pulled back toward an unmitigated fair value gap located below that major swing low. The analyst emphasizes this pullback is not a reversal but gap-filling behavior.",
  "key_observation": "An unmitigated FVG exists directly below a major swing low; when price returns to fill that FVG, it does not constitute a valid change of character or trend reversal.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identify a major swing low as the origin of a valid break of structure (BOS) in an uptrend.",
    "Step 2: Observe an unmitigated Fair Value Gap (FVG) located below that major swing low on the left side of the chart.",
    "Step 3: Note that price pulls back toward the FVG zone—not breaking below the major swing low—to fill the imbalance/inefficiency.",
    "Step 4: Conclude this FVG mitigation does not invalidate the uptrend or signal a true reversal, thus avoiding false short signals."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "Always check for unmitigated FVGs below key swing points before interpreting a break below as a reversal; price often returns to fill imbalances without changing trend direction.",
